How can I make the `dir` argument have a default of `.Right`?
In Zig, you can provide default values for function arguments by using the `=?` syntax. However, Zig does not support default arguments directly in the function signature. Instead, you can achieve this by using a wrapper function that provides the default value.

Here's how you can modify your code to provide a default value for the `dir` argument:

```zig
const Direction = @import("./direction.zig").Direction;

const Cell = [2]i32;

pub fn renderAtCell(cell: Cell, dir: Direction) void {
    //
}

pub fn renderAtCellWithDefault(cell: Cell, dir: Direction = Direction.Right) void {
    renderAtCell(cell, dir);
}
```

In this example, `renderAtCellWithDefault` is a wrapper function that calls `renderAtCell` with the provided `dir` argument or defaults to `Direction.Right` if no argument is provided. This way, you can call `renderAtCellWithDefault` without specifying the `dir` argument, and it will use the default value of `Direction.Right`.
